ðŸ’¬ MANAGEMENT SENTIMENT & TONE

â€¢ [Pattern 1]: [Confidence signals, hedging language, emphasis through repetition]
â€¢ [Pattern 2]: [Tone shifts vs prior calls, defensive signals]

WHAT TO CAPTURE:
- Conviction signals: Confident language, emphatic statements, superlatives
- Hedging signals: Cautious language, qualifiers, "we'll see," "monitoring closely"
- Emphasis patterns: Repetition of same phrase/concept across prepared remarks + Q&A
- Tone shifts: Changes from prior calls or within this call
- Defensive signals: Pushback on analyst questions, deflection

CRITICAL PATTERN DETECTION:
When management repeats same phrase/concept 3+ times, synthesize as single bullet showing repetition pattern.

Examples:
âœ“ "Confident on pricing: CEO mentioned 'pricing power' 8 times across prepared remarks and Q&A; no hedging language"
âœ“ "Conservative on guidance: CFO stated 'would never underwrite these high prints' 3 times; emphasized 'balance and discipline'"
âœ“ "Defensive on inventory: Management deflected 3 analyst questions about working capital build; attributed to 'tactical stocking'"

